    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="605"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1152 St 2/–</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-07-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 287</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 624
                    of June 14, 1926, in regard to the levy of a forced contribution, in the name of
                    the Standard Oil Company, on the native agent of the Company at K’aihsien,
                    Szechwan, by one of the local Chinese military leaders. The views expressed by
                    you on the second and third pages<note n="40" xml:id="d605fn40">Refers to second
                        paragraph of the despatch.</note> of the despatch under acknowledgment are
                    approved. With respect to the question whether grounds for protest exist in this
                    case you are informed that, in the circumstances, the Department considers that
                    a protest could properly be made.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
